    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in cp_positioning_measurement_report function\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP positioning measurement report copy function was not properly allocating memory for the copied structure, causing segmentation faults when accessing the copied data. The issue occurred when the gNB received positioning measurement reports from the DU and attempted to process them.\n\nThe bug was introduced when the positioning functionality was added but the copy function implementation was incomplete. The function signature existed but the actual memory allocation was missing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c`: Implemented proper memory allocation and copying logic in cp_positioning_measurement_report\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.h`: Added proper function declarations for positioning measurement report handling\n- `openair2/COMMON/f1ap_messages_types.h`: Added f1ap_positioning_measurement_report_t structure definition\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/CMakeLists.txt`: Added f1ap_positioning.c to build\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_lib_extern.h`: Included positioning header\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure gNB with positioning capabilities enabled\n2. Connect a UE that supports positioning measurements\n3. Trigger a positioning measurement report from the UE\n4. Observe segmentation fault when the gNB attempts to process the report\n\nThe crash occurs in the cp_positioning_measurement_report function when it tries to access fields of the copied structure that were not properly allocated.\n"
}